  "_meta": {
    "description": "Ground truth for PII masking evaluation (Weg A: counts plus positive and negative lists). Convention: occurrences, not distinct persons. names_must_mask lists personal-name tokens (given and family names) that MUST NOT appear in the masked text (recall). must_survive lists substantive terms (street names, place names, technical terms, dates, identifiers, organisation names) that MUST still appear in the masked text (precision). expected_name_count is a coarse indicator of personal-name occurrences and may differ from the masker span count.",
    "scope": "Masked types: NAME, TELEFON, EMAIL, IBAN. The corpus contains no phone numbers, emails, or IBANs; this GT exercises NAME recall and the precision of not masking substantive terms.",
    "convention_decisions": {
      "couples": "Married-couple constructions count each person. 'Ralf und Brigitte Kessler' = 2 persons per occurrence.",
      "familie_gross": "'Familie Groß' counts the family surname as a name to mask. Organisation names (Weingut Groß, Kanzlei Franken & Stein) are NOT counted as names but are placed on must_survive to detect false positives.",
      "titles": "Titles and functions (Dr., RA, Geschäftsführer, Sprecherin, Dipl.-Ing.) are not names and are ignored."
    }
  },
